0031|- [HelpText]
0032|#PLOT Y(X)=<function of X> or PLOT X(T)=f(T),Y(T)=g(T)
S   |           <             >
0033|*plots a curve.
0034|*X (and T) can be any 'word' like 'time' in PLOT Y(time)=v*time^2/2.
0035|*The plotting area is selected by the XSCALE and YSCALE specifications.
0036|*Defaults are XSCALE=-10,0,10 and YSCALE=-10,0,10.
0037|*The range of X is given by X=<initial value>,<final value>,<step>.
S   |                              <             > <           > <    >
0038|*If <step> is not given, (<final value>-<initial value>)/100 is employed
S   |    <    >                <           > <             >
0039|*as the plotting step. If no range is given, limits of XSCALE are used.
0040|*For example,
0041|*PLOT X(t)=10*cos(t),Y(t)=10*sin(t) / t=0,6.283,0.2
0042|*plots a circle of radius 10.
0044|*The functions must be written according to the rules of editorial computing.
0045|*They may include parameters whose values are given in the edit
0046|*field in the form <name of parameter>=<value>.
S   |                   <                 > <     >
0047|*For example,
0048|*PLOT Y(x)=x^n / n=1,4,1 XSCALE=-3(1)3 YSCALE=-100(50)100
0049|*plots 4 different power functions.
0050|- [New]
0051|*New options in SURVO MM described on the next page!
0052|- [/New]
0054|*In SURVO MM it is possible to give ranges of the variable (X) and
0055|*parameters also in the form <initial_value>(<step>)<final_value>.
S   |                             <             > <    > <           >
0056|*.......................................................................
0057|*Example:
0058|*GPLOT Y(x)=a*x+b / x=-5(0.01)5 a=0(0.1)1 b=-2(1)2
0059|*.......................................................................
