0069|- [HelpText]
0070|#PLOT Y(X)=<function of X> or PLOT X(T)=f(T),Y(T)=g(T)
S   |           <             >
0071|*plots a family of curves when the function(s) include parameters
0072|*whose values are given in the edit field in the form
0073|*<name of parameter>=<initial value>,<final value>,<step>.
S   | <                 > <             > <           > <    >
0074|*Several varying parameters may occur simultaneously.
0075|*For example,
0076|*PLOT X(t)=A*cos(t),Y(t)=B*sin(t) / A=1,10,1 B=1,10,1 t=0,6.283,0.2
0077|*plots a curve family consisting of 10*10=100 different ellipses.
0080|*Using data values as varying parameters:
0081|*Parameters can take their values from variables of a Survo data set, say
0082|*TEST. Such parameters, say A and B, are given in the form
0083|*   A=DATA:TEST,Result1
0084|*   B=DATA:TEST,Result2[-2]  (Result2 is lagged by 2.)
0085|*Then a curve for each active observation in TEST is plotted using
0086|*values of variable Result1 in data TEST as parameter A and similarly
0087|*values of variable Result2 (lagged by 2) in data TEST as parameter B.
0088|*Only one data set can be used in one PLOT scheme at a time.
0090|*All other varying parameters like C=0,10,1 can be used in combination
0091|*with data-dependent parameters.
0092|*................................................................................
0093|*Example 1: Circles with radius from Fibonacci sequence (DATA R):
0094|*DATA R: 1 2 3 5 8 13 21 34 55 END
0095|*GPLOT X(T)=R*COS(T),Y(T)=R*SIN(T)
0096|*R=DATA:R,R
0097|*SCALE=-60,60 SIZE=465,349 T=0,2*pi,pi/40 pi=3.141592653589793
0098|*................................................................................
0100|*Example 2: Olympic rings (See how the correct overlapping is achieved)
0101|*DATA OLYMPIC
0102|*  A   B   C   D   E        Comments
0103|* -2   0   9   1   0        Blue                A: X coord of the center
0104|*  0   0   0   1   0        Black               B: Y coord of the center
0105|*  2   0  13   1   0        Red                 C: Color
0106|* -1  -1   5   1   0        Yellow              D: Length of the arc
0107|*  1  -1  10   1   0        Green               E: Start angle of the arc
0108|* -2   0   9  0.1 -0.2      Blue over yellow
0109|*  0   0   0  0.1  4        Black over yellow
0110|*  0   0   0  0.1 -0.2      Black over green
0111|*  2   0  13  0.1  4        Red over green
0113|*GPLOT X(T)=A+R*COS(D*T+E),Y(T)=B+R*SIN(D*T+E)
0114|*R=0.90  Radius of the circles
0115|*T=[line_width(7)],0,2*pi,pi/20 pi=3.141592653589793
0116|*A=DATA:OLYMPIC,A B=DATA:OLYMPIC,B D=DATA:OLYMPIC,D E=DATA:OLYMPIC,E
0117|*XSCALE=-3,3 YSCALE=-2,1  SIZE=600,300  HOME=0,100  MODE=VGA
0118|*COLOR_CHANGE=C C=DATA:OLYMPIC,C  FRAME=0 XDIV=0,1,0 YDIV=0,1,0 HEADER=
0119|*................................................................................
0122|*Messages in plotting families of curves (screen graphics):
0123|*Especially in cases of data-dependent parameters it is useful to display
0124|*certain functions of parameters while plotting. This is possible by
0125|*using a MESSAGES specification. It has the form
0126|*MESSAGES=<list_of_message_names> where each member is a specification
S   |          <                     >
0127|*of the form <member>=<function_of_parameters>,n,x,y indicating that
S   |             <      > <                      >
0128|*this message (value of the function) is to be displayed from the
0129|*position (x,y) onwards for curves nos. n,2n,3n,4n,...
0130|*................................................................................
0131|*Example:
0132|*GPLOT X(T)=R*COS(T)+A,Y(T)=R*SIN(T)
0133|*R=1,20,1 A=1,10,1
0134|*SCALE=-30,30 SIZE=465,349 T=0,2*pi,pi/40 pi=3.141592653589793
0135|*MESSAGES=M1,M2 M1=R,20,520,330 M2=A,20,520,310
0136|*................................................................................
0137|*More extensive examples on data-dependent parameters and messages in
0138|*plotting of curve families are provided in sucros /BUFFON and /CONFMEAN.
